    echo 'Starting installation...'
    pip3 install pyspark==2.4.8 wget==3.2 pyspark2pmml==0.5.1 > install.log 2> install.log
    if [ $? == 0 ]; then
        echo 'Please <<RESTART YOUR KERNEL>> (Kernel->Restart Kernel and Clear All Outputs)'
    else
        echo 'Installation failed, please check log:'
        cat install.log
    fi
elif [ $version == '38' ] || [ $version == '39' ]; then
    pip3 install pyspark==3.1.2 wget==3.2 pyspark2pmml==0.5.1 > install.log 2> install.log
    if [ $? == 0 ]; then
        echo 'Please <<RESTART YOUR KERNEL>> (Kernel->Restart Kernel and Clear All Outputs)'
    else
        echo 'Installation failed, please check log:'
        cat install.log
    fi
else
    echo 'Currently only python 3.6, 3.7 , 3.8 and 3.9 are supported, in case you need a different version please open an issue at https://github.com/IBM/claimed/issues'
    exit -1
fi

In [5]:
parameters = list(
    map(lambda s: re.sub('$', '"', s),
        map(
            lambda s: s.replace('=', '="'),
            filter(
                lambda s: s.find('=') > -1 and bool(re.match(r'[A-Za-z0-9_]*=[.\/A-Za-z0-9]*', s)),
                sys.argv
            )
    )))

for parameter in parameters:
    logging.warning('Parameter: ' + parameter)
    exec(parameter)

indexer = StringIndexer(inputCol="class", outputCol="label")

vectorAssembler = VectorAssembler(inputCols=eval(input_columns),
                                  outputCol="features")

normalizer = MinMaxScaler(inputCol="features", outputCol="features_norm")

binEval = MulticlassClassificationEvaluator(). \
    setMetricName("accuracy"). \
    setPredictionCol("prediction"). \
    setLabelCol("label")
In [12]:
i = 1
accuracy_temp = 0.0
for target_numTrees in [10,20]:
    for target_maxDepth in [5,7]:
        rf_temp = RandomForestClassifier(numTrees=target_numTrees, maxDepth=target_maxDepth)
        print("Iteration",i,"numTrees =",target_numTrees,"maxDepth =",target_maxDepth)
        pipeline_temp = Pipeline(stages=[indexer, vectorAssembler, normalizer, rf_temp])
        model_temp = pipeline_temp.fit(df_train)
        prediction_temp = model_temp.transform(df_test)
        new_accuracy = binEval.evaluate(prediction_temp)
        print("Accuracy =",new_accuracy)
        if new_accuracy > accuracy_temp:
            accuracy_temp = new_accuracy
            print("New highest accuracy, iteration number,",i)
        print('-------------------------')
        print()
        i = i+1
